TITLE: Implementing Hooks in Cypress Tests
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use before, beforeEach, afterEach, and after hooks in Cypress tests at both root and describe block levels.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress-documentation/blob/main/docs/app/core-concepts/writing-and-organizing-tests.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
before(() => {
  // root-level hook
  // runs once before all tests
})

beforeEach(() => {
  // root-level hook
  // runs before every test block
})

afterEach(() => {
  // runs after each test block
})

after(() => {
  // runs once all tests are done
})

describe('Hooks', () => {
  before(() => {
    // runs once before all tests in the block
  })

  beforeEach(() => {
    // runs before each test in the block
  })

  afterEach(() => {
    // runs after each test in the block
  })

  after(() => {
    // runs once after all tests in the block
  })
})
```

