TITLE: Matching Routes with RouteMatcher in Cypress
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use cy.intercept() with different RouteMatcher objects to match specific HTTP requests. Examples include matching by method and URL, pathname and query parameters, and complex URL patterns.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress-documentation/blob/main/docs/api/commands/intercept.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// These both yield the same result:
cy.intercept({ method: 'GET', url: '**/users' })
cy.intercept('GET', '**/users')
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Match any type of request with the pathname `/search`
// and the query parameter 'q=some+terms'
cy.intercept({
  pathname: '/search',
  query: {
    q: 'some terms',
  },
}).as('searchForTerms')
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
cy.intercept(
  {
    // this RegExp matches any URL beginning with
    // 'http://api.example.com/' and ending with '/edit' or '/save'
    url: /^http:\/\/api\.example\.com\/.*\/(edit|save)/,
    // matching requests must also contain this header
    headers: {
      'x-requested-with': 'exampleClient',
    },
  }
)
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// this example will cause 1 request to `/temporary-error`
// to receive a network error and subsequent requests will
// not match this `RouteMatcher`
cy.intercept({ url: '/temporary-error', times: 1 }, { forceNetworkError: true })
```

