TITLE: Converting an image to a Data URL with base64 encoding in Cypress
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to request an image with base64 encoding to create a Data URI. It retrieves the content type from the response headers and constructs a complete data URI for use in the application.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress-documentation/blob/main/docs/api/commands/request.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
cy.request({
  url: 'https://docs.cypress.io/img/logo.png',
  encoding: 'base64',
}).then((response) => {
  const base64Content = response.body
  const mime = response.headers['content-type'] // or 'image/png'
  // see https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Basics_of_HTTP/Data_URIs
  const imageDataUrl = `data:${mime};base64,${base64Content}`
})
