TITLE: Opening DevTools Automatically for Different Browser Families
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to configure different browser families (chromium, firefox, electron) to automatically open developer tools when launched by Cypress.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress-documentation/blob/main/docs/api/node-events/browser-launch-api.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
on('before:browser:launch', (browser = {}, launchOptions) => {
  // `args` is an array of all the arguments that will
  // be passed to browsers when it launches
  console.log(launchOptions.args) // print all current args

  if (browser.family === 'chromium' && browser.name !== 'electron') {
    // auto open devtools
    launchOptions.args.push('--auto-open-devtools-for-tabs')
  }

  if (browser.family === 'firefox') {
    // auto open devtools
    launchOptions.args.push('-devtools')
  }

  if (browser.name === 'electron') {
    // auto open devtools
    launchOptions.preferences.devTools = true
  }

  // whatever you return here becomes the launchOptions
  return launchOptions
})
```

