TITLE: Migrating cy.wait() Response Object from cy.route() to cy.intercept()
DESCRIPTION: Shows differences in the response object structure when using cy.wait() with cy.route() versus cy.intercept(), highlighting property name changes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress-documentation/blob/main/docs/app/references/migration-guide.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_78

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Wait for XHR from cy.route()
cy.route('POST', '/users').as('createUser')
// ...
cy.wait('@createUser').then(({ requestBody, responseBody, status }) => {
  expect(status).to.eq(200)
  expect(requestBody.firstName).to.eq('Jane')
  expect(responseBody.firstName).to.eq('Jane')
})
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Wait for intercepted HTTP request
cy.intercept('POST', '/users').as('createUser')
// ...
cy.wait('@createUser').then(({ request, response }) => {
  expect(response.statusCode).to.eq(200)
  expect(request.body.name).to.eq('Jane')
  expect(response.body.name).to.eq('Jane')
})
```

