TITLE: Inefficient SSO Login Custom Command in Cypress
DESCRIPTION: An example of an inefficient custom command for SSO login that doesn't use session caching.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress-documentation/blob/main/docs/api/commands/origin.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
Cypress.Commands.add('login', (username, password) => {
  // Remember to pass in arguments via `args`
  const args = { username, password }
  cy.origin('cypress.io', { args }, ({ username, password }) => {
    // Go to https://example.cypress.com/login
    cy.visit('/login')
    cy.contains('Username').find('input').type(username)
    cy.contains('Password').find('input').type(password)
    cy.get('button').contains('Login').click()
  })
  // Confirm we're back at the primary origin before continuing
  cy.url().should('contain', '/home')
})
```

